"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: non=
e !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; borde=
r-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">  I wrote</a>:</p>
<blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">He can keep doing this! What if yo=
u give him 25% of Tesla, he sells=C2=A0<em>that</em>=C2=A0stake for billion=
s of dollars, he uses the billions of dollars to fund some new distracting =
hobby, and he comes back to you in a year saying =E2=80=9Cyeah, I don=E2=80=
=99t know, my heart isn=E2=80=99t really in Tesla anymore, maybe if you gav=
e me another 25% it would motivate me.=E2=80=9D The $55 billion pay package=
 in 2018 =E2=80=94 the one that the board is currently getting sued for =E2=
=80=94 was supposed to motivate him to focus on Tesla, and it very clearly =
had the opposite effect! It gave him too much money, which he spent on dist=
ractions. And now he needs more money to turn back to Tesla from those dist=
ractions.</p></blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Even now, Musk has good reasons for doing his =
next good idea at Tesla. It=E2=80=99s the biggest of his companies, so it h=
as a lot of capacity to do things. It=E2=80=99s the largest portion of his =
fortune, so increasing its value does the most for his wealth. It=E2=80=99s=
 the most=C2=A0<em>liquid=C2=A0</em>portion of his fortune =E2=80=94=C2=A0h=
e can sell or borrow against Tesla shares much more easily than the rest of=
 his companies =E2=80=94=C2=A0so increasing its value does the most for his=
 practical buying power. It=E2=80=99s the company with which he is, still, =
probably, most associated in the public imagination, so doing stuff at Tesl=
a probably does the most for his reputation.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">But he also has some good reasons for doing hi=
s next good idea at SpaceX or xAI or X or Neuralink or Boring Co. or a bran=
d-new startup. One is that his ownership of Tesla=C2=A0<em>has=C2=A0</em>go=
ne down (because he sold stock! to buy Twitter!), so he does capture less o=
f the value he creates there.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">But the bigger one is that at Tesla, unlike at=
 his other companies, Musk really=C2=A0<em>is=C2=A0</em>subject to rules, t=
o outside supervision. If he tweets nonsense about Tesla, the US Securities=
 and Exchange Commission <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com=
/click/34187745.258395/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGlj=
