a319a23cBe3d6c1d2" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D=
"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-=
bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid=
; background-color: #ccc;">  can punish him</a>. If he has his buddies on t=
he Tesla board pay him another $50 billion, a Delaware court can make him g=
ive the money back. His power over Tesla is, as public-company CEOs go, pre=
tty absolute: The board loves him, the shareholders love him, he doesn=E2=
=80=99t have to show up at work, they pay him $50 billion, it=E2=80=99s gre=
at. But his power over Tesla is not=C2=A0<em>that=C2=A0</em>absolute, compa=
red to running a private company without the interference of courts or the =
SEC. And he runs five private companies! I bet he is a bit fonder of them t=
oday.=C2=A0</p>
